Article-I.D.: news.1992Aug13.184912.24025
Sender: usenet@news.acns.nwu.edu (Usenet on news.acns)
Organization: Northwestern University, Evanston Illinois.
Lines: 555

Hi everyone!

Game 8, and two more to go. :-)

This game is dedicated to our dearest *UFO 30k*, probably/perhaps/maybe the
"strongest 30k" in the solar system (he once claimed to be from Mars :-).

That's not all about UFO; he's one of the most special because he was the
organizer of IGSWCT '92.  The tournament offered a great chance for players
to meet some opponents never faced before, and thus to make more friends on
IGS, so it was probably one of the most precious experience for many of the
participants.  But this would have been impossible without our
"UnForgettable Orginizer."

Fact: IGSWCT '92 had a total of over 300 games, while an NFL (pro football)
regular season consists only 224 games. :)

Nice job, UFO!

jzy, NR ^_^

